# Java & stack-specific specification

Language-agnostic **naming, formatting, collections, concurrency, control flow, comments, tests, errors, SQL, layering, dependencies, security, documentation layout**: **Design guidelines** in `cursorrules/common`. Below: **Java / MyBatis / Spring / this repo** only.

## Naming (Java & layered model)

- **Classes** nouns in `UpperCamelCase`, except domain suffixes **DO / BO / DTO / VO** as adopted by the project.
- **Methods, parameters, fields, locals**: `lowerCamelCase`.
- **Packages**: lowercase, **one English word per segment**, singular.
- **Arrays**: brackets on the type (`String[]`), not after the name.
- **Boolean fields**: no `is` prefix in Java names; map carefully if DB columns use `is_xxx`.
- **Abstract** classes start with `Abstract` or `Base`; **exceptions** end with `Exception`; **tests** `{Target}Test`.
- **Interfaces** for **Service / DAO**; implementations end with `Impl`. Capability-style interfaces use **adjective** names; **no** default modifiers on interface methods; **only constants** as interface fields.
- **Enums** end with `Enum`; enum members **UPPER_CASE**.
- **Service/DAO methods**: `get` / `list` / `count` / `insert` / `delete` / `update`.
- Domain types: **`*DO`, `*DTO`, `*VO`**; do not use **`*POJO`**.
- **QO** lives at the **controller** layer; controllers map QO в†’ model via structure mapping, then pass the model into **service**.

## Constants (Java literals)

- Use uppercase **`L`** for `long` literals (e.g. `1L`).

## Formatting (Java)

- Prefer **`import`** over fully qualified class names unless names collide.

## OOP (Java)

- Access **static** members via the **class name**.
- **@Override** on all overridden methods.
- **varargs** only when parameters share type and meaning.
- Do **not** change method signatures in place; use **@Deprecated** with explanation; do not call deprecated APIs.
- **equals**: null-safe patterns; use **equals** (not `==`) for **wrapper** types.
- **POJO** members: **no** field default values in the sense of this guide; **serialVersionUID** only when compatibility strategy requires change.
- **No business logic in constructors**; use an explicit **init** path.
- **POJO** implements **toString**.
- **String.split**: check bounds before indexed access.
- Group **constructors** and overloads; order methods **public в†’ protected в†’ private в†’ getters/setters**.
- **Setter** parameter names match fields; **StringBuilder** (or equivalent) for repeated string append in loops.
- Use **`final`** where appropriate; **clone**: beware shallow copy; enforce **access levels** per team rules.

## Collections (Java SE)

- Do **not** mutate **keySet() / values() / entrySet()** views to add elements.
- **subList** is a view; do **not** cast to **ArrayList**; avoid changing backing list size while a subList is live.
- **List в†’ array**: `toArray(T[])`.
- Do **not** structurally modify the list from **Arrays.asList**.
- Respect **`<? extends T>` / `<? super T>`** for APIs you expose or consume.

## Concurrency (Java)

- Prefer **ThreadPoolExecutor** over **Executors** factory shortcuts for pools.
- **SimpleDateFormat** is not thread-safe; use **java.time** or other safe APIs.
- **ThreadLocal.remove()** when work finishes.
- **Double-checked locking**: use **volatile** (or better, **init-on-demand holder** / concurrent utilities) as appropriate.
- Prefer **ThreadLocalRandom** over shared **Random**; **AtomicInteger**, **LongAdder**, etc. where they fit.
- Mind **HashMap** concurrent resize pitfalls; prefer **ConcurrentHashMap** when concurrent mutation is real.

## Flow control (Java + services)

- **switch**: every case ends with **break/return**; **default** required.
- **Braces** on all control statements.
- Document **where** parameter validation may be skipped vs required (controller vs service vs model).

## Comments (Javadoc)

- **Javadoc** on classes, fields, and methods; **required** on abstract/interface methods.
- Every class: **author** and **date** in Javadoc.
- **Enumeration** constants: Javadoc each value.

## Templates & misc (Java ecosystem)

- **Velocity**: use POJO property names; **`$!{var}`** for null-safe output; keep templates thin.
- **Random**: **nextInt** / **nextLong**, not **`Math.random() * N`** for integer ranges.
- **Timestamps**: **`System.currentTimeMillis()`** where that is the project standard.

# Exception and Logs (Java)

## Exception

- Do **not** catch **JDK unchecked** runtime exceptions to вЂњhandleвЂќ; use **preconditions** instead.
- **RPC** boundary: use **return codes** as the project defines; **application** code uses **exceptions**.
- Use **domain-specific** exception types, not generic throws.

## Logs

- Facade: **SLF4J** API, not **Log4j/Logback** types directly in app code.
- Retain log files **в‰Ґ 15 days**.
- File pattern: **`app_logType_logName.log`**.
- **Logger additivity**: **false** where the project configures appenders.
- Log **every branch entry** at the level the runbook requires (team standard).

# MySQL Rules (this project)

## Table Schema Rules

- Boolean-like columns: **`is_xxx`** with **unsigned tinyint**; exception **`is_deleted`**.
- Table/column names: lowercase letters, digits, underscores; **no plural table names**; no reserved keywords.
- Index names: **`pk_` / `uk_` / `idx_`**.
- Decimals: **`decimal`**, not float/double.
- Fixed length в†’ **char**; **varchar** length в‰¤ 5000.
- **Relation** tables suffix **`_rel`**.
- **`id`**: unsigned int/long, values start from **10_000_000**.
- **`ct` / `ut` / `dt`**: unsigned int, **UNIX seconds**; **`is_deleted`** same numeric family as **`id`**, default **0**.
- Prefer **defaults** on columns; comments in **English**.

## Index Rules

- (Unique vs non-unique, **varchar** prefix length, **LIKE** + pagination, **ORDER BY** vs index, covering indexes, late join for offsets, **EXPLAIN** goals, composite column order: **SQL and relational access** in `common`.)

## SQL Rules (project policy)

- **No** foreign keys with cascading updates; **no** stored procedures.
- (Aggregate nullability, `COUNT(*)` vs `COUNT(col)`, paging short-circuit, `SELECT` before corrective DML, `IN` size, row caps, `EXPLAIN` discipline: **SQL and relational access** in `common`.)

## ORM (MyBatis-Plus / XML)

- Explicit column list; **no `SELECT *`**.
- **Boolean** POJO fields: naming vs DB **`is_`** вЂ” explicit **mapping**.
- **No `resultClass`**; **DO + resultMap**.
- **No `${}`** interpolation for user-controlled fragments.
- **No** ORM paging that loads the full table into memory.
- **No HashMap/Hashtable** as row types; use **DO**s.
- **`gmt_modified`** (or project equivalent) updates with the row.
- Avoid вЂњupdate everythingвЂќ APIs and **excessive @Transactional**.
- Know **MyBatis** `isEqual` / `isNotEmpty` / `isNotNull` semantics.

